<br>
Here's a good example of why this system is not only bias but extrememly unfair to any non melee class.  Say you are camping the Necrosis/Guardian spawn in sebilis.  This spawn has absolutely NO loot for a caster class.  Say a CSS drops from the Necrosis.  NB4G the tank, ranger, rogue automatically gets the item, I'm screwed.  I can spend 10 hrs at this camp and not get a damn thing way of thinking.  If I random for this at least I have a chance to sell the item and get something I can use.  Most caster loot from Kunark is EXTREMELY expensive.  IF I want an ornate rune shield I pay 30k for it.  It would take me winning 2 CSS to even come close to affording that.<br>
<br>
Why do you see high lvl warriors running around with 200k in their bank and high lvl wizards having barely 5k in their bank?  The answer is NB4G.  I wholly expect to random any and all items that drop in a camp unless it has been specifically stated before hand.  I tend to see people change their tone when it's a camp that their loot drops and you'll see most melee prefer the NB4G, but when I'm playing my warrior or rogue I fully expect to have to random for anything my class can use.  A warrior can do just like I have to do, when he wins something he can't use he can go to the auction and get somethign he can use.<br>
<br>
This whole lame idea of being greedy if you are randoming on something you can't use is totally lame.  Every item in the game has a value at the auction, warriors don't deserve cobalt any more than I deserve a bonecasters robe.<br>
<br>
Anyone that believe they have any more right over an item than I do, should take a step back and realize who the real &quot;GREEDY&quot; person is. <p>Zotreth Beion'Dhevel<br>
