<br>
Zotreth, if you don't have a chance at loot, why stay?  Why bother to continue working with people for 10 hours?  Is exp in that camp really worth it to you?  I realize you didn't have much choice pre-Velious, but you certainly do now.<br>
<br>
I can't dispute your claim of 5% caster loot in Kunark, but I don't think it's correct either.  I'll agree it's heavily favored to the melees.  Let's say your claim is true.  Why does it matter if you get loot?  There isn't much you can trade for anyway.<br>
<br>
I think you are being a bit misleading in asking why are there Warriors with 200k in the bank.  I could ask the same of Clerics, Enchanters, Rangers, Druids, Necros, Shaman, Paladins, Wizards, Mages, Bards, Rogues, and Monks.  I know members of every class with huges sums in the bank.  Unless you know the bank account total of every character in EQ, it's a bit of stretch to say one class usually has more cash than another.<br>
<br>
FWIW, I prefer NBG.  I realize it can be abused, but I still feel it's a better policy.  However, I am adaptable for the situation as long as it is stated up front. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
